{
  "name": "Locus: Meteoric Filings",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to a weapon.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>A crystal vial with dark metal filings within. </p><p>While attuned the vial and its filings merges magically merges with a <strong>weapon</strong> of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, requires 10 minutes to complete and it upon completion leaves a faintly visible layer of iron-like dust on the surface of the weapon. Once completed, the weapon becomes magical for the purpose of overcoming resistances.</p><p><strong>Effect:</strong> While attuned, the filings coat the magnetic dust that is always being pulled.  When the weapon deals damage to a creature that has resistance or immunity to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing from Nonmagical Attacks that are not Silvered or Adamantine they are instead vulnerable to this weapon's damage. This vulnerability is only to the bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage from this weapon. Features that add damage without a type (and are implied to be the weapon's damage like Sneak Attack) are also part of the vulnerable damage.</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> This can be applied to magical hand wraps, brass knuckles and other similar items that would represent Unarmed Strikes.  The Unarmed Strikes would the be considered the weapon and these Unarmed Strikes would be what benefits from the item.</p>",
